HEADWORD: Butyrometer
<hw>Bu`ty*rom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>butyrum</ets> butter + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument
for determining the amount of fatty matter or butter contained in a
sample of milk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

